{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"1240b1b2-bff6-46bb-936b-87513c37a707","content":"Update these three files:\n\n**1. `*.csproj`** — change the target framework:\n```xml\n<TargetFramework>net11.0</TargetFramework>\n```\n\n**2. `global.json`** — pin the new SDK:\n```json\n{ \"sdk\": { \"version\": \"11.0.100\" } }\n```\n\n**3. `Dockerfile`** — update base images:\n```dockerfile\nFROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/aspnet:11.0 AS base\nFROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/sdk:11.0 AS build\n```\n\nThen run:\n```bash\ndotnet restore\ndotnet build\n```\n\nReview any **breaking changes** in the [.NET 11 release notes](https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/dotnet/core/whats-new/) and update deprecated APIs or NuGet packages (e.g., `Microsoft.AspNetCore.*` or `Microsoft.Extensions.*`) to their 11.x versions.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"c80d4d4a-ce6b-45f9-8b80-fac39c988033","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking how to update their .NET 10 ASP.NET Core web app to .NET 11. This is a straightforward knowledge question - I don't need to search any codebase since they're describing their setup generically.\n\nLet me provide concise guidance on updating the three files they mentioned.","outputTokens":326,"requestId":"2834:1B1DA8:347170:3E433C:69EACA2D"},"id":"3114a419-4e49-492f-82ca-c2e700979719","timestamp":"2026-04-24T01:41:08.319Z","parentId":"9ca65167-a5bc-4fd7-a2ea-a4aad3d4d482"}
